{{Flavour|This powerful ring can be activated to hide its wearer from the view of others, but increases the speed of his or her metabolism greatly while doing so.}}

Wearing a [[ring of invisibility]] grants you the [[Evoke Invisibility]] [[ability]], allowing you to turn [[invisible]] at will. It requires a high [[Evocations]] skill to use reliably or for a long duration, but there are no penalties for failing to evoke it, so even low-level characters can make some use of it. However, invisibility's benefits come with significant [[hunger]] and potential [[magic contamination]] costs, and are less dramatic than one might expect.

This ring also grants its wearer the ability to become visible at will, a useful option when trying to minimize magic contamination.

The chance of successfully evoking this ring rises with your [[Evocations]] skill:

{{#invoke:Failure rate table|table|Evocations|60|2}}

==Strategy==
*A character with a high [[Stealth]] skill can benefit from use of a ring of invisibility by dealing extra [[stabbing]] damage to enemies who cannot see you. This is by no means a long-term strategy, however, as many mid- to late-game monsters can [[see invisible]]. You can find a list of monsters which see through invisibility [[:Category:See invisible|here]]. 

==See Also==
*[[Invisible]]

==History==
In [[0.18]], rings of invisibility were removed.

